Dialogue: 0,0:00:22.52,0:00:25.17,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.67,0:00:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome to What's New In tvOS?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:27.89,0:00:29.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm Hans, and I'm an engineer on
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.36,0:00:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,the tvOS Team.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:30.80,0:00:32.32,Default,,0,0,0,,This morning, with my colleague
Dialogue: 0,0:00:32.32,0:00:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Marshall, I'd like to talk to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:33.77,0:00:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you about some of the
Dialogue: 0,0:00:34.44,0:00:35.99,Default,,0,0,0,,enhancements and new APIs in
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.99,0:00:36.32,Default,,0,0,0,,tvOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:36.32,0:00:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to do this in two
Dialogue: 0,0:00:38.48,0:00:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,parts, beginning with updates on
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.79,0:00:42.99,Default,,0,0,0,,the overall SDK.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:42.99,0:00:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to take a look at
Dialogue: 0,0:00:44.67,0:00:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,system-wide improvements, and
Dialogue: 0,0:00:46.31,0:00:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,then narrow down to individual
Dialogue: 0,0:00:47.75,0:00:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,widgets.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.90,0:00:50.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, Marshall will talk to you
Dialogue: 0,0:00:50.66,0:00:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,about some of the new APIs
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.26,0:00:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,around view controllers.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:54.53,0:00:55.39,Default,,0,0,0,,We have a lot of ground to
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.39,0:00:56.70,Default,,0,0,0,,cover, so let's get started.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:58.08,0:01:00.26,Default,,0,0,0,,First, is ODR or On Demand
Dialogue: 0,0:01:00.26,0:01:00.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Resources.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.08,0:01:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,For those of you, new to ODR, it
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.41,0:01:04.67,Default,,0,0,0,,allows your app to keep its
Dialogue: 0,0:01:04.67,0:01:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,resources in the App Store,
Dialogue: 0,0:01:05.97,0:01:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of including in the App
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.17,0:01:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Bundle.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:08.27,0:01:09.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, your app can download
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.69,0:01:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,them as they become needed.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.75,0:01:13.51,Default,,0,0,0,,This helps your app to download
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.51,0:01:16.34,Default,,0,0,0,,fast, launch quickly, while
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.34,0:01:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,still providing very
Dialogue: 0,0:01:17.31,0:01:18.35,Default,,0,0,0,,high-quality content to the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.35,0:01:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,users.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:19.28,0:01:20.88,Default,,0,0,0,,And all of this, without taking
Dialogue: 0,0:01:20.88,0:01:22.36,Default,,0,0,0,,up a lot of local storage on the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.36,0:01:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,customer's device at any given
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.00,0:01:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,time.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:26.46,0:01:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Last year, there was an upper
Dialogue: 0,0:01:28.19,0:01:30.99,Default,,0,0,0,,bound to your app bundle at 200
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.99,0:01:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,megabytes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:32.49,0:01:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,This helped your app to be very
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.77,0:01:35.40,Default,,0,0,0,,lean, and ultimately, your
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.40,0:01:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,customers were able to start
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.73,0:01:38.12,Default,,0,0,0,,using your app that much sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.46,0:01:40.67,Default,,0,0,0,,But since then, we have received
Dialogue: 0,0:01:40.67,0:01:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,many requests that this limit be
Dialogue: 0,0:01:42.78,0:01:43.28,Default,,0,0,0,,increased.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:43.98,0:01:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in tvOS 10.2, we increased
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.40,0:01:48.58,Default,,0,0,0,,this to over 20 times at 4
Dialogue: 0,0:01:48.58,0:01:49.15,Default,,0,0,0,,gigabytes.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.81,0:01:52.26,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you have an existing
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.26,0:01:53.45,Default,,0,0,0,,project that conformed to the
Dialogue: 0,0:01:53.45,0:01:55.67,Default,,0,0,0,,old limit, and you have some
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.67,0:01:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,resources that you wish you
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.82,0:01:57.99,Default,,0,0,0,,could have included in the app
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.99,0:01:59.52,Default,,0,0,0,,bundle, the new limit will
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.52,0:02:00.53,Default,,0,0,0,,enable you to do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.66,0:02:03.95,Default,,0,0,0,,First, go to the Asset Catalog,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.23,0:02:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and select the resource that you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.32,0:02:07.56,Default,,0,0,0,,want to move back into the app
Dialogue: 0,0:02:07.56,0:02:07.87,Default,,0,0,0,,bundle.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.87,0:02:10.41,Default,,0,0,0,,And at the bottom of attributes
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.41,0:02:12.15,Default,,0,0,0,,inspector, simply delete the
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.15,0:02:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,tags.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:13.68,0:02:15.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this resource is bundled,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.85,0:02:17.27,Default,,0,0,0,,so at runtime, you can directly
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.27,0:02:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,access it without first having
Dialogue: 0,0:02:18.90,0:02:20.09,Default,,0,0,0,,to make the bundle resource
Dialogue: 0,0:02:20.09,0:02:21.35,Default,,0,0,0,,request for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:22.22,0:02:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, this increase
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.04,0:02:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,does not come at the cost of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.00,0:02:27.34,Default,,0,0,0,,counting towards the rest of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:27.34,0:02:29.58,Default,,0,0,0,,your asset pack allowance, which
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.93,0:02:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,remains the same at 20
Dialogue: 0,0:02:30.97,0:02:31.60,Default,,0,0,0,,gigabytes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:31.76,0:02:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, now, the combined size of
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.55,0:02:35.46,Default,,0,0,0,,your app bundle and content can
Dialogue: 0,0:02:35.46,0:02:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,be up to 24 gigabytes.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.94,0:02:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is a lot of content.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:39.89,0:02:41.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And we believe it will help you
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.59,0:02:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,make your app's user experience
Dialogue: 0,0:02:43.11,0:02:44.18,Default,,0,0,0,,even richer than before.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.25,0:02:47.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's ODR in tvOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.99,0:02:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, we're thrilled to report
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.96,0:02:53.73,Default,,0,0,0,,that beginning tvOS 11, RTL or
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.73,0:02:54.77,Default,,0,0,0,,right to left languages, are
Dialogue: 0,0:02:54.77,0:02:55.57,Default,,0,0,0,,fully supported.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.09,0:02:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if your app looked like this
Dialogue: 0,0:02:58.89,0:03:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,in English, it will look like
Dialogue: 0,0:03:00.97,0:03:04.04,Default,,0,0,0,,this in Arabic, and like this in
Dialogue: 0,0:03:04.04,0:03:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Hebrew.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.06,0:03:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, your text will
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.02,0:03:09.95,Default,,0,0,0,,flow right to left, and most of
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.95,0:03:11.73,Default,,0,0,0,,your user interface will appear
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.73,0:03:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically mirrored.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:13.60,0:03:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you're used to supporting
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.63,0:03:18.02,Default,,0,0,0,,RTL in iOS or macOS, you'll be
Dialogue: 0,0:03:18.02,0:03:19.52,Default,,0,0,0,,pleased to know that everything
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.52,0:03:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,works the exact same way on tvOS
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.26,0:03:21.79,Default,,0,0,0,,as well.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:22.39,0:03:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you're not, we have a few
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.43,0:03:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,recommendations.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.36,0:03:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,First, is to use based
Dialogue: 0,0:03:28.25,0:03:29.20,Default,,0,0,0,,internationalization.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:30.42,0:03:31.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Base internationalization
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.30,0:03:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,separates string localization
Dialogue: 0,0:03:33.64,0:03:35.37,Default,,0,0,0,,from UI layout, so while you're
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.37,0:03:36.38,Default,,0,0,0,,working on the UI, your
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.80,0:03:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,localization expert can continue
Dialogue: 0,0:03:38.42,0:03:39.91,Default,,0,0,0,,to translate the strings without
Dialogue: 0,0:03:39.91,0:03:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,worrying about interfering with
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.68,0:03:42.12,Default,,0,0,0,,the layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.12,0:03:45.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And all new projects are created
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.27,0:03:47.26,Default,,0,0,0,,with base internationalization
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.26,0:03:48.26,Default,,0,0,0,,turned on by default.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:48.68,0:03:49.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you're starting anew,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:50.15,0:03:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,you're already there.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:51.41,0:03:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you have an existing
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.51,0:03:54.61,Default,,0,0,0,,project that has yet to take
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.61,0:03:56.25,Default,,0,0,0,,advantage of this, you can go to
Dialogue: 0,0:03:56.25,0:03:57.92,Default,,0,0,0,,the Project Info, and check the
Dialogue: 0,0:03:57.92,0:03:59.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Use Base Internationalization
Dialogue: 0,0:03:59.29,0:04:02.09,Default,,0,0,0,,checkbox to start using it.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:03.02,0:04:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, is to use Auto Layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.54,0:04:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In particular, leading and
Dialogue: 0,0:04:07.14,0:04:09.62,Default,,0,0,0,,trailing attributes instead of
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.62,0:04:11.05,Default,,0,0,0,,left or right when creating the
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.05,0:04:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,constraint.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.87,0:04:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,This is so that when the system
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.93,0:04:16.05,Default,,0,0,0,,lays out the UI, it can infer
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.05,0:04:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the appropriate left or right
Dialogue: 0,0:04:17.51,0:04:18.87,Default,,0,0,0,,directions based on the current
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.87,0:04:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,language direction.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.21,0:04:24.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, constantly test
Dialogue: 0,0:04:24.17,0:04:25.41,Default,,0,0,0,,your layout during development.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:26.30,0:04:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And to help you with this,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.70,0:04:28.79,Default,,0,0,0,,there's an option in Scheme
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.79,0:04:29.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Settings where you can
Dialogue: 0,0:04:29.99,0:04:31.42,Default,,0,0,0,,temporarily set the application
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.42,0:04:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,language.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:33.24,0:04:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can set it to Arabic,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:35.23,0:04:37.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Hebrew, or even right to left
Dialogue: 0,0:04:37.67,0:04:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,pseudo language, which simply
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.04,0:04:40.22,Default,,0,0,0,,flips the direction without
Dialogue: 0,0:04:40.22,0:04:41.38,Default,,0,0,0,,changing the actual language.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.77,0:04:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, RTL support is new in tvOS
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.67,0:04:46.64,Default,,0,0,0,,this year, but it has been
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.64,0:04:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,around for iOS and macOS for a
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.83,0:04:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,number of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.38,0:04:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And previous years' sessions
Dialogue: 0,0:04:51.62,0:04:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,have great guidelines and best
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.87,0:04:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,practices that now apply to
Dialogue: 0,0:04:54.47,0:04:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,tvOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.34,0:04:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we highly recommend that you
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.42,0:04:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,check them out.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.42,0:05:00.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, RTL support is
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.54,0:05:01.77,Default,,0,0,0,,built into TVML.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.77,0:05:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you're using TVML
Dialogue: 0,0:05:03.04,0:05:04.39,Default,,0,0,0,,templates in your app, you'll
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.39,0:05:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,get all the right behaviors for
Dialogue: 0,0:05:05.52,0:05:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,free.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.32,0:05:11.38,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's RTL support in tvOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.47,0:05:13.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, is Safe Area.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.64,0:05:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Many TVs use Overscan in some
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.08,0:05:18.57,Default,,0,0,0,,shape or form, creating a
Dialogue: 0,0:05:18.57,0:05:20.26,Default,,0,0,0,,situation where not all the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.26,0:05:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,pixels are displayed to the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.32,0:05:21.73,Default,,0,0,0,,user.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:22.93,0:05:24.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in the past, we have
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.32,0:05:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,recommended that you manually
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.61,0:05:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,compensate for this by insetting
Dialogue: 0,0:05:29.05,0:05:30.17,Default,,0,0,0,,your view's content.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.28,0:05:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,And the API to assist you was
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.79,0:05:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,UIScrollView.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.54,0:05:36.18,Default,,0,0,0,,overscanCompensationInsets.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.86,0:05:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This provided you with the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.87,0:05:39.84,Default,,0,0,0,,values that you can then plug
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.84,0:05:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,into your view or view
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.76,0:05:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,controller's configuration code.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.50,0:05:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,TVOS 11 introduces a more,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.95,0:05:49.79,Default,,0,0,0,,robust framework for you to make
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.79,0:05:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,sure your content is within the
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.34,0:05:53.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Safe Area, with much less work.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.12,0:05:56.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for example, some properties
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.09,0:05:57.36,Default,,0,0,0,,are automatically updated for
Dialogue: 0,0:05:57.36,0:05:57.52,Default,,0,0,0,,you.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.01,0:06:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Your view's safeAreaInsets is
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.98,0:06:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,updated as it moves in and out
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.94,0:06:03.78,Default,,0,0,0,,of the view hierarchy.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:04.89,0:06:09.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And your view's safeLayoutGuide
Dialogue: 0,0:06:09.74,0:06:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is also updated as the Safe Area
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.32,0:06:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Inset changes.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:13.40,0:06:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can also customize your
Dialogue: 0,0:06:15.31,0:06:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,own things, by using UIView
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.24,0:06:18.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller's
Dialogue: 0,0:06:18.82,0:06:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,additionalSafeAreaInsets.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.11,0:06:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And the values you specify here,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:23.01,0:06:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,will be added when calculating
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.82,0:06:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,the Safe Area Insets of the View
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.26,0:06:27.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller's view.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.96,0:06:31.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Now when you link your app
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.08,0:06:33.12,Default,,0,0,0,,against tvOS 11, your app will
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.12,0:06:34.49,Default,,0,0,0,,be subject to the new behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.58,0:06:36.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And we highly recommend that you
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.56,0:06:39.22,Default,,0,0,0,,take opportunity to audit your
Dialogue: 0,0:06:39.22,0:06:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,app, and adjust the layout in
Dialogue: 0,0:06:41.11,0:06:42.33,Default,,0,0,0,,the context of these new APIs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:42.33,0:06:45.25,Default,,0,0,0,,There was a session yesterday,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:45.74,0:06:47.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Updating Your App for iOS 11,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.94,0:06:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,that goes into this very topic
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.38,0:06:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,in depth.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:49.71,0:06:52.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we recommend you check it
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.97,0:06:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,out.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:54.29,0:06:56.42,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you have a view or view
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.42,0:06:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,controller that manually
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.45,0:06:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,compensates for Overscan, and it
Dialogue: 0,0:06:59.11,0:07:01.37,Default,,0,0,0,,does so in a rather delicate
Dialogue: 0,0:07:01.37,0:07:02.67,Default,,0,0,0,,way, and you're hesitant to
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.67,0:07:05.26,Default,,0,0,0,,touch it just yet, you can opt
Dialogue: 0,0:07:05.26,0:07:06.65,Default,,0,0,0,,out of the new behavior on the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.65,0:07:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,view or view controller basis.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:09.56,0:07:13.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And to do this, there are Insets
Dialogue: 0,0:07:13.04,0:07:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Layout Margins from Safe Area
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.54,0:07:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,for your view, and view respects
Dialogue: 0,0:07:18.36,0:07:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,system minimum layout margins
Dialogue: 0,0:07:19.82,0:07:20.73,Default,,0,0,0,,for your view controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.33,0:07:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And our own experience suggests
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.34,0:07:25.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that oftentimes, it's your
Dialogue: 0,0:07:25.82,0:07:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,scroll view that requires some
Dialogue: 0,0:07:27.85,0:07:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,of your attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.26,0:07:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So, for scroll views, there is
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.15,0:07:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Content Inset Adjustment
Dialogue: 0,0:07:33.31,0:07:33.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.97,0:07:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And by setting this to Never,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.60,0:07:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,you're effectively opting out
Dialogue: 0,0:07:38.10,0:07:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,your scroll view to the new
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.15,0:07:39.59,Default,,0,0,0,,behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:40.21,0:07:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's Safe Area.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.30,0:07:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, is updating your app's
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.27,0:07:49.85,Default,,0,0,0,,data in the background.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.85,0:07:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Last year, we brought user
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.53,0:07:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,notification framework to the
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.90,0:07:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,tvOS, so you can send remote or
Dialogue: 0,0:07:55.72,0:07:57.03,Default,,0,0,0,,push notifications to your app.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:57.03,0:07:58.95,Default,,0,0,0,,But there was one notable
Dialogue: 0,0:07:58.95,0:07:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,aspect.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:00.46,0:08:01.44,Default,,0,0,0,,When the system received
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.44,0:08:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,multiple notifications while
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.68,0:08:04.90,Default,,0,0,0,,your app is not running, it only
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.90,0:08:06.61,Default,,0,0,0,,delivered the very last one and
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.61,0:08:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that, when the app is explicitly
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.74,0:08:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,launched by the user.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.88,0:08:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is improving.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:12.87,0:08:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In tvOS 11, when a notification
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.78,0:08:17.77,Default,,0,0,0,,is received by the system, the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:17.77,0:08:19.44,Default,,0,0,0,,system wakes your app in the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.44,0:08:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,background, and delivers it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:22.57,0:08:23.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And this provides an effective
Dialogue: 0,0:08:23.79,0:08:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,means for what's called a silent
Dialogue: 0,0:08:25.78,0:08:26.43,Default,,0,0,0,,notification.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.03,0:08:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,A silent notification is a
Dialogue: 0,0:08:30.05,0:08:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,notification that wakes up your
Dialogue: 0,0:08:32.34,0:08:33.96,Default,,0,0,0,,app in the background, so it can
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.96,0:08:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,do some work transparently for
Dialogue: 0,0:08:35.31,0:08:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the user.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.25,0:08:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,That's where the word "silent"
Dialogue: 0,0:08:37.38,0:08:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,comes from.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:39.27,0:08:40.25,Default,,0,0,0,,And by using silent
Dialogue: 0,0:08:40.25,0:08:42.60,Default,,0,0,0,,notification, you can
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.60,0:08:43.87,Default,,0,0,0,,periodically download new
Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.87,0:08:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,content, refresh your app's
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.01,0:08:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,data, or even set up to alert
Dialogue: 0,0:08:48.09,0:08:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,the user in the app, when the
Dialogue: 0,0:08:49.34,0:08:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,app enters foreground.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.56,0:08:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to configure your app to
Dialogue: 0,0:08:53.27,0:08:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,process silent notification,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.05,0:08:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,first, add remote notifications
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.57,0:08:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,background mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:59.58,0:09:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, make your app
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.28,0:09:02.87,Default,,0,0,0,,delegate, the user notification
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.87,0:09:03.51,Default,,0,0,0,,center delegate.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:05.62,0:09:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,And register to receive remote
Dialogue: 0,0:09:07.16,0:09:07.86,Default,,0,0,0,,notifications.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.38,0:09:10.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And then user notification
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.97,0:09:11.94,Default,,0,0,0,,center did receive with
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.94,0:09:14.22,Default,,0,0,0,,completion handler, do the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.89,0:09:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's silent notifications.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.82,0:09:20.85,Default,,0,0,0,,The second way of updating your
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.85,0:09:22.40,Default,,0,0,0,,app's data in the background is
Dialogue: 0,0:09:22.40,0:09:23.78,Default,,0,0,0,,through a mechanism called
Dialogue: 0,0:09:23.90,0:09:24.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Background Fetch.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:26.20,0:09:28.74,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if your app needs to for
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.74,0:09:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,example, periodically check for
Dialogue: 0,0:09:30.76,0:09:33.39,Default,,0,0,0,,new content, it can register for
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.39,0:09:34.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Background Fetch.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.02,0:09:36.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Then the system, when it deems
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.76,0:09:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,an opportunity arises for you,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:39.56,0:09:40.73,Default,,0,0,0,,wakes it up in the background.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:41.85,0:09:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Your app can then initiate a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:43.49,0:09:44.84,Default,,0,0,0,,fetch operation and do the work.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:45.30,0:09:48.14,Default,,0,0,0,,To configure your app to do a
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.14,0:09:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Background Fetch, first add
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.72,0:09:51.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Background Fetch Background
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.82,0:09:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Mode, and then, in your app
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.41,0:09:55.86,Default,,0,0,0,,delegate, register for
Dialogue: 0,0:09:55.86,0:09:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Background Fetch.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.21,0:10:00.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, in your application
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.43,0:10:01.65,Default,,0,0,0,,perform Fetch with Completion
Dialogue: 0,0:10:01.65,0:10:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Handler, implement the work, and
Dialogue: 0,0:10:03.87,0:10:05.10,Default,,0,0,0,,don't forget to call the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:05.10,0:10:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Completion Handler with the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.02,0:10:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,fetch result.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.82,0:10:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's Background Fetch.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:10.14,0:10:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And as you can see, tvOS11
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.17,0:10:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,provides two new ways of
Dialogue: 0,0:10:13.43,0:10:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,updating your app's data.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:15.86,0:10:17.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Often, you know exactly when new
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.87,0:10:19.34,Default,,0,0,0,,data is available for your app,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.60,0:10:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's when you call silent
Dialogue: 0,0:10:21.63,0:10:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,notification.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:23.60,0:10:25.14,Default,,0,0,0,,On the other hand, it's the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:25.14,0:10:26.85,Default,,0,0,0,,system that knows, "When is the
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.85,0:10:28.17,Default,,0,0,0,,best time to check for updates
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.17,0:10:28.69,Default,,0,0,0,,for your app?"
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.69,0:10:30.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And this is because it not only
Dialogue: 0,0:10:30.90,0:10:32.09,Default,,0,0,0,,looks into its own resource
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.09,0:10:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,availability, but also takes
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.14,0:10:35.94,Default,,0,0,0,,into account user behaviors such
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.94,0:10:38.09,Default,,0,0,0,,as which apps the user has been
Dialogue: 0,0:10:38.09,0:10:39.12,Default,,0,0,0,,using most frequently.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.45,0:10:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So, to take advantage of that,
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.67,0:10:43.98,Default,,0,0,0,,register for Background Fetch.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.40,0:10:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And we hope you take advantage
Dialogue: 0,0:10:46.96,0:10:48.35,Default,,0,0,0,,of these new ways to make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:10:48.35,0:10:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,your app is up to date, even
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.30,0:10:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,before it enters the foreground.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:52.07,0:10:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's Background Update.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.52,0:10:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:10:59.88,0:11:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, is scrolling.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:02.96,0:11:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,When a scroll view has a large
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.36,0:11:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,amount of content, it is often
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.97,0:11:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,tedious, if not frustrating, to
Dialogue: 0,0:11:07.45,0:11:08.99,Default,,0,0,0,,scroll through them all, to get
Dialogue: 0,0:11:08.99,0:11:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,to the exact item you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:11.33,0:11:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in tvOS 10.2, we introduced
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.02,0:11:15.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Accelerated Scrolling to help
Dialogue: 0,0:11:15.46,0:11:16.91,Default,,0,0,0,,users scroll more efficiently.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.54,0:11:21.80,Default,,0,0,0,,To enter the accelerated
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.80,0:11:24.20,Default,,0,0,0,,scrolling mode, all it takes is
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.20,0:11:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,a few large swipes in the same
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.55,0:11:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,direction on the touch pad.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.06,0:11:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally, the user can swipe
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.50,0:11:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,on the far-right edge of the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:34.70,0:11:36.37,Default,,0,0,0,,touch pad, to browse through the
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.37,0:11:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,indices.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.59,0:11:40.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And the good news for us
Dialogue: 0,0:11:40.75,0:11:42.13,Default,,0,0,0,,developers, is that we don't
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.13,0:11:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,have to do any additional work
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.39,0:11:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to get this new behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.95,0:11:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it's built into any
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.39,0:11:49.38,Default,,0,0,0,,scroll views, including table
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.38,0:11:51.48,Default,,0,0,0,,views, or even collection views.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.94,0:11:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And this behavior is always on,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:55.02,0:11:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can't turn it off.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:57.09,0:11:58.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are some things you
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.12,0:11:59.58,Default,,0,0,0,,can customize to make sure that
Dialogue: 0,0:11:59.58,0:12:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,your scroll view works well
Dialogue: 0,0:12:01.05,0:12:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,within your design.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.26,0:12:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, by default, the index bar
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.07,0:12:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,appears as you enter the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:08.95,0:12:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,accelerated scrolling mode.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:10.77,0:12:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,But you can completely hide this
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.67,0:12:14.30,Default,,0,0,0,,by overriding the Index Display
Dialogue: 0,0:12:14.30,0:12:18.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Mode to Hidden.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:18.14,0:12:19.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, the default scroll
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.57,0:12:21.03,Default,,0,0,0,,indicator style works really
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.03,0:12:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,well because it adapts to the
Dialogue: 0,0:12:22.50,0:12:24.61,Default,,0,0,0,,view controllers light or dark
Dialogue: 0,0:12:24.75,0:12:26.04,Default,,0,0,0,,user interface style.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.04,0:12:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,But if your design requires you
Dialogue: 0,0:12:29.78,0:12:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,to have an explicit style, you
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.19,0:12:32.70,Default,,0,0,0,,can override this to black or
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.70,0:12:35.63,Default,,0,0,0,,white, and then do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:36.94,0:12:39.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally, you can customize
Dialogue: 0,0:12:39.36,0:12:40.78,Default,,0,0,0,,the index titles for your table
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.78,0:12:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,views by using the two data
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.31,0:12:42.72,Default,,0,0,0,,[inaudible] methods.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.44,0:12:45.13,Default,,0,0,0,,First, to get the array of index
Dialogue: 0,0:12:45.13,0:12:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,titles, and to get the index for
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.89,0:12:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,a given index title.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.57,0:12:53.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Similarly, for collection view,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:54.30,0:12:55.64,Default,,0,0,0,,you can get the array of index
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.64,0:12:57.85,Default,,0,0,0,,titles and get the index path
Dialogue: 0,0:12:58.05,0:12:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for a given index title.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.61,0:13:02.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's updates in Scroll
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.10,0:13:02.42,Default,,0,0,0,,View.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.80,0:13:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, is a new button type,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:07.03,0:13:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,UIButtonTypePlain.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.85,0:13:10.24,Default,,0,0,0,,But before that, let's take a
Dialogue: 0,0:13:10.24,0:13:11.22,Default,,0,0,0,,look at the system button.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.52,0:13:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,UIButtonTypeSystem provides
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.79,0:13:16.61,Default,,0,0,0,,interactive focus effect when
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.61,0:13:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,the button is in focus, and
Dialogue: 0,0:13:18.69,0:13:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,background blur when it isn't.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:20.65,0:13:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The background blur, provides
Dialogue: 0,0:13:23.00,0:13:24.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the affordance of a button and
Dialogue: 0,0:13:24.62,0:13:26.52,Default,,0,0,0,,also, enhances the legibility of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:26.52,0:13:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,the title.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.46,0:13:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,It is one of the most widely
Dialogue: 0,0:13:29.90,0:13:31.87,Default,,0,0,0,,used controls in tvOS, which is
Dialogue: 0,0:13:31.87,0:13:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps why we have heard from
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.47,0:13:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,many of you that you'd like to
Dialogue: 0,0:13:34.58,0:13:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,customize this a little bit
Dialogue: 0,0:13:35.58,0:13:37.80,Default,,0,0,0,,more, to add a background color,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.80,0:13:38.40,Default,,0,0,0,,for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.47,0:13:41.52,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in tvOS 11, we're making a
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.52,0:13:42.25,Default,,0,0,0,,new button type,
Dialogue: 0,0:13:42.56,0:13:43.59,Default,,0,0,0,,UIButtonTypePlain.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.17,0:13:47.67,Default,,0,0,0,,A plain type button has all of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.67,0:13:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,the interactive focus effect of
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.04,0:13:51.12,Default,,0,0,0,,a system button, but without the
Dialogue: 0,0:13:51.12,0:13:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,background blur, which lends
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.88,0:13:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,itself to full customization.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.03,0:13:57.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And using a plain type button is
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.87,0:13:58.67,Default,,0,0,0,,straightforward.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.20,0:14:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,First, create the button with
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.99,0:14:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,UIButtonTypePlain, and continue
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.27,0:14:06.49,Default,,0,0,0,,customizing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.30,0:14:09.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's the plain type
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.72,0:14:10.91,Default,,0,0,0,,button.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.32,0:14:11.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.52,0:14:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.05,0:14:16.83,Default,,0,0,0,,The last set of enhancements in
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.83,0:14:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,this first part, is around
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.01,0:14:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,UIImageView.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:21.66,0:14:24.26,Default,,0,0,0,,On tvOS, interactive focus
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.26,0:14:25.16,Default,,0,0,0,,effect is an important
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.16,0:14:25.61,Default,,0,0,0,,technique.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:26.25,0:14:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It gives your users a sense that
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.21,0:14:28.89,Default,,0,0,0,,they're connected with the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.89,0:14:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,screen, and also tells them
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.71,0:14:32.13,Default,,0,0,0,,exactly where their focus is.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.68,0:14:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And most often, we use floating,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.77,0:14:36.16,Default,,0,0,0,,layered images to maximize the
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.16,0:14:36.52,Default,,0,0,0,,effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.22,0:14:39.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Since it was first introduced,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.19,0:14:41.70,Default,,0,0,0,,many of you have asked for a way
Dialogue: 0,0:14:41.70,0:14:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to customize this further, by
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.73,0:14:45.43,Default,,0,0,0,,adding your own content at
Dialogue: 0,0:14:45.43,0:14:46.98,Default,,0,0,0,,runtime, so they can participate
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.98,0:14:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,in the focus effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.22,0:14:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,In tvOS 11, we're introducing an
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.24,0:14:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,easy and safe way to do that,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:52.44,0:14:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's Image Overlay.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.22,0:14:57.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Image Overlay uses a new
Dialogue: 0,0:14:57.20,0:14:58.87,Default,,0,0,0,,property, Overlay Content View,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.69,0:15:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,which is similar in concept to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:00.96,0:15:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,the content view in table view
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.71,0:15:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,or collection view cells, in
Dialogue: 0,0:15:04.08,0:15:05.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that that's where you add your
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.52,0:15:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,content as sub-views.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:07.14,0:15:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,By default, overlay content view
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.59,0:15:12.12,Default,,0,0,0,,clips its child views to the
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.12,0:15:15.03,Default,,0,0,0,,image views bounds, but you can
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.03,0:15:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,override this and draw outside
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.45,0:15:17.97,Default,,0,0,0,,of it, by setting the clips to
Dialogue: 0,0:15:17.97,0:15:19.71,Default,,0,0,0,,bounds of the overlay content
Dialogue: 0,0:15:19.71,0:15:20.80,Default,,0,0,0,,view to false.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.84,0:15:24.14,Default,,0,0,0,,The next improvement in
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.14,0:15:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,UIImageView is in Alpha Channel
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.85,0:15:26.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Support.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.44,0:15:30.94,Default,,0,0,0,,As you know, layered image are
Dialogue: 0,0:15:30.94,0:15:32.36,Default,,0,0,0,,required to have an opaque
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.36,0:15:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,background.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:34.20,0:15:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And even floating -- flat single
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.27,0:15:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,layered images, for floating
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.82,0:15:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,effect, they are also required
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.80,0:15:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to have an opaque background.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.57,0:15:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,In tvOS 11, that is no longer
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.04,0:15:45.51,Default,,0,0,0,,the case.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.34,0:15:48.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can now have arbitrary
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.21,0:15:50.10,Default,,0,0,0,,shape alpha-channel, and for
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.10,0:15:51.37,Default,,0,0,0,,some of you, this might scream
Dialogue: 0,0:15:52.23,0:15:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,non-rectangular shadows.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.30,0:15:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,So, instead of just talking
Dialogue: 0,0:15:55.22,0:15:56.97,Default,,0,0,0,,about this, I'd like to ask my
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.97,0:15:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,colleague Paul to show us in a
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.15,0:15:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.78,0:15:59.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:00.52,0:16:03.84,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.34,0:16:07.76,Default,,0,0,0,,>> So, yes, I'd like to demo
Dialogue: 0,0:16:09.01,0:16:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,some of the new features of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.89,0:16:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,UIImageView in tvOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.36,0:16:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I've been working on this simple
Dialogue: 0,0:16:15.72,0:16:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,video playing app here.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:16.98,0:16:18.20,Default,,0,0,0,,I liked they had a couple of new
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.20,0:16:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,features.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.40,0:16:21.09,Default,,0,0,0,,The first thing I like to do, is
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.09,0:16:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,add an icon to the poster to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.50,0:16:23.48,Default,,0,0,0,,make it obvious that when you
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.48,0:16:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,select the poster, the video
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.93,0:16:25.64,Default,,0,0,0,,will start playing.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.22,0:16:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And I also like to add a
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.94,0:16:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,progress bar, to the posters of
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.11,0:16:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,the videos that I've started
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.96,0:16:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,watching.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:30.30,0:16:31.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And that way, I can quickly see
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.09,0:16:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,how far through the videos I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.55,0:16:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'm just going to add some
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.42,0:16:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,views to the image view of the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.35,0:16:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,poster to implement that UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.04,0:16:43.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can see that the UI
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.26,0:16:44.54,Default,,0,0,0,,shows up, but it feels pretty
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.54,0:16:45.95,Default,,0,0,0,,disconnected from the image
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.95,0:16:46.82,Default,,0,0,0,,that's moving behind it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.50,0:16:49.51,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'd really like for that UI
Dialogue: 0,0:16:49.51,0:16:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,to move along with the image.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:52.47,0:16:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Luckily, that's easy to do in
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.11,0:16:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,tvOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.85,0:16:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of adding those views to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:57.46,0:16:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,my image view, I'm just going to
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.86,0:16:59.81,Default,,0,0,0,,add them to the image view's
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.87,0:17:00.76,Default,,0,0,0,,overlay content view.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.38,0:17:03.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Build and run and see how that
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.24,0:17:04.36,Default,,0,0,0,,looks.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:06.34,0:17:07.62,Default,,0,0,0,,That's more like the effect I
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.62,0:17:08.31,Default,,0,0,0,,was going for.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.52,0:17:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.43,0:17:16.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the UI moves along with the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.25,0:17:17.66,Default,,0,0,0,,image, as if it was another
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.66,0:17:18.95,Default,,0,0,0,,layer in the layered image.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.76,0:17:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And the next thing I'd like to
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.29,0:17:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,do is add some gadgets to these
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.61,0:17:24.40,Default,,0,0,0,,posters, and that way I can mark
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.40,0:17:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,videos that might be new or
Dialogue: 0,0:17:25.80,0:17:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,otherwise interesting to the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.83,0:17:27.19,Default,,0,0,0,,user.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.00,0:17:29.09,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm just going to add a
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.09,0:17:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,touch button to the app that
Dialogue: 0,0:17:30.14,0:17:31.31,Default,,0,0,0,,will let me toggle those badges
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.31,0:17:33.58,Default,,0,0,0,,on and off so they can make sure
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.58,0:17:35.35,Default,,0,0,0,,the UI's working the way I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.40,0:17:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,To make that touch button, I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:17:38.07,0:17:40.02,Default,,0,0,0,,going to make a button of type
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.15,0:17:41.84,Default,,0,0,0,,custom, so that I don't get
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.84,0:17:42.79,Default,,0,0,0,,system chrome that you
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.79,0:17:43.89,Default,,0,0,0,,ordinarily get with a button.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.73,0:17:45.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm going to set the
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.60,0:17:48.18,Default,,0,0,0,,button's image view to adjust
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.18,0:17:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,image when ancestor focused, and
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.00,0:17:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that way it'll get the nice,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:50.98,0:17:52.20,Default,,0,0,0,,floating effect when the button
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.20,0:17:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,becomes focused.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:53.56,0:17:54.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And I'm going to use the same
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.56,0:17:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,image for the button that I'll
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.80,0:17:57.98,Default,,0,0,0,,use for the actual badges
Dialogue: 0,0:17:57.98,0:17:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.84,0:18:00.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And the badge image, has a
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.92,0:18:02.02,Default,,0,0,0,,circular alpha channel.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:02.73,0:18:05.22,Default,,0,0,0,,And in tvOS 11, that works well
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.22,0:18:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,with the floating effect of the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.58,0:18:07.73,Default,,0,0,0,,shadow and the spotlight and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.31,0:18:09.05,Default,,0,0,0,,work the way that you would
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.05,0:18:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,expect.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:09.42,0:18:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,When I tap the button, I'm going
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.09,0:18:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,to add the badge image to the
Dialogue: 0,0:18:13.66,0:18:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,overlay content view of these
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.82,0:18:15.29,Default,,0,0,0,,posters.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.70,0:18:16.50,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll see how that looks.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.12,0:18:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,We can see that there's a
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.01,0:18:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,problem.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:19.74,0:18:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The badge is there in the upper
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.70,0:18:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,left corner, but it's being
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.39,0:18:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,clipped to the transformed frame
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.29,0:18:24.96,Default,,0,0,0,,of the image view.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.65,0:18:26.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And often, that's exactly what
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.73,0:18:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,you want for your overlays.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.28,0:18:29.37,Default,,0,0,0,,In this case, it's not what I
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.37,0:18:29.66,Default,,0,0,0,,want.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.31,0:18:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Luckily, I was listening to
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.34,0:18:32.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Hans' talk, and he let me know
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.64,0:18:33.36,Default,,0,0,0,,how to fix this.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:34.36,0:18:35.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just going to set clips to
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.44,0:18:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,bounce to false on the overlay
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.98,0:18:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,content view.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:37.64,0:18:40.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's try that one more time.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.54,0:18:44.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I'll toggle the badges on.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.15,0:18:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what I was I hoping to
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.53,0:18:45.83,Default,,0,0,0,,see.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.31,0:18:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So, now the badges draw the way
Dialogue: 0,0:18:47.36,0:18:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I want them to.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.42,0:18:49.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And then continue to move with
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.56,0:18:50.82,Default,,0,0,0,,the image along with the rest of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:50.82,0:18:50.98,Default,,0,0,0,,the UI.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.52,0:18:56.59,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.09,0:18:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So, that's just a quick look at
Dialogue: 0,0:18:58.49,0:18:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,some of the new features of
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.64,0:19:01.62,Default,,0,0,0,,UIImageView in tvOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:01.79,0:19:03.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Back to you, Hans.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:04.03,0:19:06.03,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.05,0:19:06.50,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thanks, Paul.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:07.59,0:19:08.74,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a great demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:09.26,0:19:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And that was enhancements in
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.93,0:19:11.60,Default,,0,0,0,,UIImageView.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.07,0:19:16.47,Default,,0,0,0,,We have just looked at seven new
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.54,0:19:17.61,Default,,0,0,0,,enhancements in tvOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.61,0:19:19.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But there are many more
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.47,0:19:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,enhancements in iOS that also
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.29,0:19:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,apply to tvOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.52,0:19:25.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Among them, we think one
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.55,0:19:26.97,Default,,0,0,0,,deserves a special attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.09,0:19:28.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And for that, I'd like to invite
Dialogue: 0,0:19:28.73,0:19:30.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Dan from the Media Framework's
Dialogue: 0,0:19:30.05,0:19:32.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Team to tell us all about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:33.52,0:19:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.24,0:19:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thanks, Hans.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:39.70,0:19:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, I'm going to take a few
Dialogue: 0,0:19:43.43,0:19:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,minutes to talk about what's new
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.11,0:19:50.22,Default,,0,0,0,,in AVKit in tvOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:50.22,0:19:52.70,Default,,0,0,0,,AVKit provides standard,
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.70,0:19:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,interactive video playback for
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.57,0:19:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,all apps on tvOS.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.92,0:20:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Includes, scrubbing, skipping,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.49,0:20:04.12,Default,,0,0,0,,scanning, and a variety of
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.12,0:20:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,advanced features like
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.21,0:20:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,interstitials, and content
Dialogue: 0,0:20:06.46,0:20:07.17,Default,,0,0,0,,proposals.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.40,0:20:09.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we talked about the basics
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.56,0:20:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,last year, so if you need to
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.92,0:20:12.41,Default,,0,0,0,,catch up, you can watch the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:12.41,0:20:15.24,Default,,0,0,0,,AVKit on tvOS session from last
Dialogue: 0,0:20:15.24,0:20:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,year.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.39,0:20:17.62,Default,,0,0,0,,And here we have
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.97,0:20:21.87,Default,,0,0,0,,AVPlayerViewController providing
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.91,0:20:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the standard video playback, in
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.20,0:20:24.16,Default,,0,0,0,,this case, showing scrubbing.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.80,0:20:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And advanced features include
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.69,0:20:31.06,Default,,0,0,0,,custom content proposals, which
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.06,0:20:32.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we introduced last year.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:32.73,0:20:35.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's talk about what's new
Dialogue: 0,0:20:35.98,0:20:36.99,Default,,0,0,0,,in tvOS 11.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.67,0:20:40.83,Default,,0,0,0,,When you want to play static
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.83,0:20:43.00,Default,,0,0,0,,images, such as a logo or a hint
Dialogue: 0,0:20:43.00,0:20:45.33,Default,,0,0,0,,or other information on top of
Dialogue: 0,0:20:45.33,0:20:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,your video but below the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.44,0:20:48.88,Default,,0,0,0,,playback controls, you use the
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.88,0:20:50.33,Default,,0,0,0,,overlay view.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.75,0:20:54.60,Default,,0,0,0,,In tvOS 11, we're introducing a
Dialogue: 0,0:20:54.60,0:20:57.38,Default,,0,0,0,,new layout guide, the Unobscured
Dialogue: 0,0:20:57.38,0:21:00.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Content Guide, which indicates
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.56,0:21:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,what portion of the screen you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.78,0:21:04.43,Default,,0,0,0,,can use for your static content,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.43,0:21:06.99,Default,,0,0,0,,without overlaying the playback
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.99,0:21:08.49,Default,,0,0,0,,controls or hints.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.73,0:21:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Here we see where the unobscured
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.86,0:21:14.33,Default,,0,0,0,,content guide lays.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:14.33,0:21:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,As you can see, the hint -- the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.00,0:21:17.14,Default,,0,0,0,,swipe down for info hint is
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.14,0:21:18.47,Default,,0,0,0,,above it.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.47,0:21:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,The bottom edge of the layout
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.06,0:21:21.89,Default,,0,0,0,,guide goes right against the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.89,0:21:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,transfer bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.82,0:21:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,But you do notice that the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.85,0:21:27.73,Default,,0,0,0,,scrubbing thumbnail however is
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.73,0:21:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,not included in that excluded
Dialogue: 0,0:21:29.91,0:21:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,region.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.16,0:21:34.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If your content is in the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.23,0:21:35.27,Default,,0,0,0,,overlay view, it'll be
Dialogue: 0,0:21:35.27,0:21:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,underneath that scrubbing
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.91,0:21:37.21,Default,,0,0,0,,thumbnail.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.21,0:21:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, let's talk about the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.73,0:21:43.52,Default,,0,0,0,,transfer bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:44.76,0:21:46.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of you have content, logos,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.54,0:21:48.32,Default,,0,0,0,,or what have you, that you want
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.32,0:21:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,to show at the same time that
Dialogue: 0,0:21:49.88,0:21:51.24,Default,,0,0,0,,the transfer bar is visible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.62,0:21:54.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Or perhaps you have something
Dialogue: 0,0:21:54.02,0:21:55.22,Default,,0,0,0,,like a channel logo that you
Dialogue: 0,0:21:55.22,0:21:56.54,Default,,0,0,0,,want to hide or get out of the
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.54,0:21:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,way when the playback controls
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.84,0:21:58.39,Default,,0,0,0,,are visible.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.54,0:22:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,You can do both of these things
Dialogue: 0,0:22:01.56,0:22:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,with the transfer bar animation
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.78,0:22:03.34,Default,,0,0,0,,coordinator.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:03.56,0:22:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,To use it, you simply implement
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.72,0:22:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,the delegate method.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.63,0:22:07.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Player View Controller will
Dialogue: 0,0:22:07.78,0:22:09.10,Default,,0,0,0,,transition to visibility of
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.10,0:22:10.54,Default,,0,0,0,,transfer bar with coordinator.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:11.61,0:22:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And you add your animations.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.67,0:22:18.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, in this example, we are --
Dialogue: 0,0:22:18.89,0:22:20.16,Default,,0,0,0,,we have a logo image view and
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.16,0:22:21.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to hide it or show
Dialogue: 0,0:22:21.93,0:22:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,it with the transfer bar.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.78,0:22:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, by no means are you limited
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.76,0:22:28.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to this.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:28.29,0:22:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You could reverse that
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.25,0:22:30.52,Default,,0,0,0,,visibility and hide it instead
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.52,0:22:31.25,Default,,0,0,0,,of showing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.72,0:22:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,You could have an additional
Dialogue: 0,0:22:33.32,0:22:35.85,Default,,0,0,0,,animation where your view slides
Dialogue: 0,0:22:35.85,0:22:37.13,Default,,0,0,0,,in from the side, for example,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:37.33,0:22:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or whatever you can -- you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.03,0:22:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, we're giving you greater
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.11,0:22:43.62,Default,,0,0,0,,control over controlling
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.15,0:22:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,dismissal with three new
Dialogue: 0,0:22:47.30,0:22:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,delegate methods.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.14,0:22:51.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And these are Player View
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.65,0:22:54.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller should dismiss, will
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.98,0:22:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,begin dismissal transition, and
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.50,0:22:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,did end dismissal transition.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.08,0:23:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,In many instances, Player View
Dialogue: 0,0:23:03.38,0:23:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller can provide an
Dialogue: 0,0:23:04.78,0:23:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,automatic transition when it's
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.35,0:23:08.02,Default,,0,0,0,,presented or dismissed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:08.16,0:23:10.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If you simply present or dismiss
Dialogue: 0,0:23:10.75,0:23:12.79,Default,,0,0,0,,it, it can fade in and fade out.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.25,0:23:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If you embed the view in your
Dialogue: 0,0:23:15.54,0:23:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,own view as a thumbnail for
Dialogue: 0,0:23:17.49,0:23:19.77,Default,,0,0,0,,example, it can automatically
Dialogue: 0,0:23:19.77,0:23:21.29,Default,,0,0,0,,zoom out and automatically zoom
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.29,0:23:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,it back when it's dismissed.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:23.73,0:23:25.67,Default,,0,0,0,,However, in some cases, you may
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.67,0:23:26.89,Default,,0,0,0,,have some sort of custom
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.89,0:23:29.97,Default,,0,0,0,,presentation where AVKit isn't
Dialogue: 0,0:23:29.97,0:23:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,going to be able to provide a
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.19,0:23:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,reasonable transition and you
Dialogue: 0,0:23:32.95,0:23:34.06,Default,,0,0,0,,need to do it yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.06,0:23:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the way you can do that
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.58,0:23:37.14,Default,,0,0,0,,now is, by implementing the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.14,0:23:40.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Should Dismiss method, and here
Dialogue: 0,0:23:40.08,0:23:41.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you would implement your
Dialogue: 0,0:23:41.89,0:23:45.69,Default,,0,0,0,,transition and return False to
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.69,0:23:47.54,Default,,0,0,0,,indicate that AVKit should not
Dialogue: 0,0:23:47.54,0:23:49.47,Default,,0,0,0,,provide the standard transition.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.20,0:23:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,When AVKit does provide the
Dialogue: 0,0:23:53.19,0:23:55.15,Default,,0,0,0,,transition, it will also call
Dialogue: 0,0:23:55.15,0:23:57.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the Will Begin Dismissal and Did
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.53,0:23:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,End Dismissal transition
Dialogue: 0,0:23:58.69,0:23:59.17,Default,,0,0,0,,methods.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.57,0:24:01.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So, at the beginning and at the
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.27,0:24:02.37,Default,,0,0,0,,end of animation.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:02.37,0:24:03.36,Default,,0,0,0,,So, you can perform whatever
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.36,0:24:04.79,Default,,0,0,0,,operations you want to do there,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.41,0:24:07.45,Default,,0,0,0,,such as controlling the playback
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.45,0:24:08.12,Default,,0,0,0,,rate for example.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:09.06,0:24:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The info views, are shown when
Dialogue: 0,0:24:11.96,0:24:13.70,Default,,0,0,0,,the user swipes down during
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.70,0:24:14.47,Default,,0,0,0,,video playback.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:15.44,0:24:16.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And the standard info views
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.80,0:24:20.02,Default,,0,0,0,,provide a variety of interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.02,0:24:22.17,Default,,0,0,0,,things, including metadata,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.17,0:24:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,navigation markers, subtitle
Dialogue: 0,0:24:24.43,0:24:26.22,Default,,0,0,0,,controls, and audio options, as
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.22,0:24:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,you can see here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:27.97,0:24:30.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, a lot of you would like to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.30,0:24:32.18,Default,,0,0,0,,have your own controls here.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.18,0:24:33.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And so, I'm pleased to announce
Dialogue: 0,0:24:33.47,0:24:35.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that we are introducing custom
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.43,0:24:36.21,Default,,0,0,0,,info views.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:36.47,0:24:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,In tvOS 11, you can provide a
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.04,0:24:39.26,Default,,0,0,0,,custom info view as you can see
Dialogue: 0,0:24:39.26,0:24:39.98,Default,,0,0,0,,in this example.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.52,0:24:44.81,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:24:45.31,0:24:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So, all you need to do is create
Dialogue: 0,0:24:47.21,0:24:48.83,Default,,0,0,0,,your own UIView Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:49.54,0:24:50.61,Default,,0,0,0,,You need determine the contents
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.61,0:24:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:52.37,0:24:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Set the custom Info View
Dialogue: 0,0:24:53.52,0:24:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller Property of your
Dialogue: 0,0:24:54.66,0:24:56.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Player View Controller, and
Dialogue: 0,0:24:57.71,0:24:58.79,Default,,0,0,0,,that's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:58.79,0:25:01.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we ask that you keep your
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.31,0:25:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,style consistent with the other
Dialogue: 0,0:25:02.85,0:25:04.17,Default,,0,0,0,,info views so that the user
Dialogue: 0,0:25:04.17,0:25:07.22,Default,,0,0,0,,won't feel out of place or
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.22,0:25:07.89,Default,,0,0,0,,confused.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:07.89,0:25:08.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And to that end, we have some
Dialogue: 0,0:25:08.92,0:25:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,guidelines.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:10.81,0:25:13.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So, first, use the standard font
Dialogue: 0,0:25:13.43,0:25:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,styles.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:14.73,0:25:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, keep your view
Dialogue: 0,0:25:17.25,0:25:19.31,Default,,0,0,0,,background transparent so that
Dialogue: 0,0:25:19.31,0:25:20.28,Default,,0,0,0,,the effect's view will show
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.28,0:25:20.62,Default,,0,0,0,,through.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:21.85,0:25:23.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You can indicate the desired
Dialogue: 0,0:25:23.02,0:25:24.68,Default,,0,0,0,,height of your info view, using
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.68,0:25:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,auto layout, which is the best
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.17,0:25:26.68,Default,,0,0,0,,way to do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:26.68,0:25:27.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you prefer, you can
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.97,0:25:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,override Preferred Content Size
Dialogue: 0,0:25:29.61,0:25:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,on your View Controller instead.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.51,0:25:34.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And regardless of which of those
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.70,0:25:37.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you use, keep your content to no
Dialogue: 0,0:25:37.44,0:25:39.11,Default,,0,0,0,,more than half of the height of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.11,0:25:41.29,Default,,0,0,0,,the screen because you don't get
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.29,0:25:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to use the entire screen.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.11,0:25:44.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And as for controls, while, you
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.75,0:25:46.45,Default,,0,0,0,,can use whatever you want, we
Dialogue: 0,0:25:46.45,0:25:47.99,Default,,0,0,0,,would recommend that you avoid
Dialogue: 0,0:25:47.99,0:25:49.17,Default,,0,0,0,,things like text fields and
Dialogue: 0,0:25:49.17,0:25:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,buttons, which feel out of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.60,0:25:53.06,Default,,0,0,0,,place, and instead prefer things
Dialogue: 0,0:25:53.06,0:25:54.57,Default,,0,0,0,,like collection and table views.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.11,0:25:58.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, finally, I'd like to
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.02,0:25:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,talk about Live Streams.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:00.46,0:26:04.97,Default,,0,0,0,,We're adding four new metadata
Dialogue: 0,0:26:04.97,0:26:07.30,Default,,0,0,0,,identifiers in tvOS 11 that lets
Dialogue: 0,0:26:07.30,0:26:09.63,Default,,0,0,0,,you specify the starting date
Dialogue: 0,0:26:09.71,0:26:11.31,Default,,0,0,0,,and ending date of your live
Dialogue: 0,0:26:11.31,0:26:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,stream or your event stream.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.90,0:26:19.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as an example, one example
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.58,0:26:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,where you want to use the exact
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.93,0:26:23.17,Default,,0,0,0,,end date, would be something
Dialogue: 0,0:26:23.33,0:26:25.10,Default,,0,0,0,,like a traditional broadcast
Dialogue: 0,0:26:25.10,0:26:26.37,Default,,0,0,0,,stream, where you have a
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.37,0:26:27.88,Default,,0,0,0,,continuous live stream that's
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.88,0:26:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,broken up into scheduled blocks
Dialogue: 0,0:26:29.89,0:26:31.74,Default,,0,0,0,,of 30 minutes or 60 minutes.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:32.62,0:26:34.17,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that case, you can use
Dialogue: 0,0:26:34.17,0:26:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,the exact start and exact end
Dialogue: 0,0:26:35.69,0:26:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,dates to indicate what part of
Dialogue: 0,0:26:37.89,0:26:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,that program you're watching
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.15,0:26:39.61,Default,,0,0,0,,right now.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:39.61,0:26:43.53,Default,,0,0,0,,How about the approximate end
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.53,0:26:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,date?
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.90,0:26:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, the easiest example there
Dialogue: 0,0:26:45.59,0:26:46.88,Default,,0,0,0,,would something like a sporting
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.88,0:26:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,event where you know for example
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.91,0:26:51.28,Default,,0,0,0,,that the game will probably last
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.28,0:26:52.64,Default,,0,0,0,,about three hours, but you
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.64,0:26:54.53,Default,,0,0,0,,really have no idea up front how
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.53,0:26:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,long it's going to go.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.35,0:26:57.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It could end sooner.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.10,0:26:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,It could end later.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:57.82,0:26:59.92,Default,,0,0,0,,And in that case, you use an
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.92,0:27:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,approximate end date.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.90,0:27:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In either case, the transfer of
Dialogue: 0,0:27:03.42,0:27:05.34,Default,,0,0,0,,our timescale will reflect these
Dialogue: 0,0:27:05.34,0:27:05.91,Default,,0,0,0,,dates.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.22,0:27:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it will either reflect more
Dialogue: 0,0:27:08.08,0:27:08.94,Default,,0,0,0,,time or less time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.15,0:27:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,When you provide exact values,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:12.35,0:27:13.29,Default,,0,0,0,,those are displayed on the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.29,0:27:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,transfer bar with a clock time
Dialogue: 0,0:27:15.21,0:27:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and approximate values are not
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.88,0:27:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,shown, so that these are --
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.85,0:27:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,isn't misled into thinking it's
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.42,0:27:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,going to end precisely at the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:20.98,0:27:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,end time.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.77,0:27:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And this helps to orient the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:25.01,0:27:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,user to where they are in your
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.26,0:27:26.63,Default,,0,0,0,,program.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.63,0:27:27.85,Default,,0,0,0,,How much they've missed, how
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.85,0:27:31.10,Default,,0,0,0,,much they should expect to have
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.88,0:27:33.74,Default,,0,0,0,,before the program is over.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:34.41,0:27:38.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's just to visualize
Dialogue: 0,0:27:38.58,0:27:41.43,Default,,0,0,0,,that, this -- in the case where
Dialogue: 0,0:27:41.43,0:27:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,you have a live stream, and you
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.73,0:27:44.66,Default,,0,0,0,,haven't specified either a start
Dialogue: 0,0:27:44.66,0:27:45.73,Default,,0,0,0,,or an end date, you get the
Dialogue: 0,0:27:45.73,0:27:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,default or legacy behavior.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.43,0:27:50.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Now in the past, this differs a
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.68,0:27:52.04,Default,,0,0,0,,little bit from what we did in
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.04,0:27:53.36,Default,,0,0,0,,tvOS 10, because in the past, we
Dialogue: 0,0:27:53.36,0:27:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,showed the start and the end
Dialogue: 0,0:27:55.39,0:27:56.10,Default,,0,0,0,,times.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:56.71,0:27:57.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We no longer do that because
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.70,0:27:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,they're both approximate.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.65,0:28:00.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But you would have a 30-minute
Dialogue: 0,0:28:00.87,0:28:01.33,Default,,0,0,0,,window.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.52,0:28:03.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in this example, it would
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.40,0:28:05.90,Default,,0,0,0,,run from 11 to 11:30, and so the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:05.90,0:28:08.25,Default,,0,0,0,,11:28 mark is near the end.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.54,0:28:11.32,Default,,0,0,0,,However, now that's fine if your
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.32,0:28:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,program actually from 11 to
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.65,0:28:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,11:30, but what if it doesn't?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.07,0:28:14.99,Default,,0,0,0,,What if it's -- you're in the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.99,0:28:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,middle of a three-hour baseball
Dialogue: 0,0:28:16.66,0:28:17.33,Default,,0,0,0,,game or something?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.09,0:28:20.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, here's an example with
Dialogue: 0,0:28:20.35,0:28:22.24,Default,,0,0,0,,exact start and end dates, in
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.24,0:28:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,this case, 10 o'clock to 1
Dialogue: 0,0:28:23.71,0:28:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,o'clock, 11:28 you see is now
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.93,0:28:28.38,Default,,0,0,0,,roughly in the middle, and the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.38,0:28:29.53,Default,,0,0,0,,scale has been adjusted.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.09,0:28:31.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, we can set an
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.56,0:28:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,approximate end date instead and
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.43,0:28:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,that just makes the end time
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.11,0:28:35.55,Default,,0,0,0,,disappear.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:36.02,0:28:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But the scale remains the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.66,0:28:42.11,Default,,0,0,0,,So, let's look briefly at the
Dialogue: 0,0:28:42.11,0:28:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,code for this.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.15,0:28:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've seen last year's
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.38,0:28:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,session, the new metadata item
Dialogue: 0,0:28:47.71,0:28:48.61,Default,,0,0,0,,helper function will look
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.61,0:28:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,familiar.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.11,0:28:50.90,Default,,0,0,0,,All we're going to do is we're
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.90,0:28:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,going to create our start dates.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.42,0:28:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to create a metadata
Dialogue: 0,0:28:54.82,0:28:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,item for it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:57.04,0:28:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to do the same thing
Dialogue: 0,0:28:58.60,0:28:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,for our end date.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.48,0:29:02.94,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, we're going to add
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.94,0:29:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,our two metadata items to our
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.83,0:29:06.70,Default,,0,0,0,,player item, to the external
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.70,0:29:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,metadata property.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.23,0:29:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, now we're going to try
Dialogue: 0,0:29:12.60,0:29:13.30,Default,,0,0,0,,a brief demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.99,0:29:15.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I've got a few things I can show
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.37,0:29:15.65,Default,,0,0,0,,here.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.82,0:29:21.75,Default,,0,0,0,,First, here's our Unobscured
Dialogue: 0,0:29:21.75,0:29:22.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Content Guide.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.33,0:29:28.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And, if we let it fade out, it
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.15,0:29:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,fades with it, because I'm using
Dialogue: 0,0:29:29.59,0:29:30.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the transfer bar animation
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.53,0:29:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,coordinator.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.00,0:29:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it fades out quickly.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.84,0:29:36.98,Default,,0,0,0,,I feel like I should wave at
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.98,0:29:37.57,Default,,0,0,0,,myself.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.26,0:29:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And here we have a custom info
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.45,0:29:42.74,Default,,0,0,0,,view.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:43.44,0:29:47.76,Default,,0,0,0,,As we saw earlier, and we can
Dialogue: 0,0:29:47.76,0:29:49.72,Default,,0,0,0,,switch it from -- to -- let's
Dialogue: 0,0:29:49.78,0:29:51.58,Default,,0,0,0,,put it on exact dates.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.37,0:29:52.95,Default,,0,0,0,,And there we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.88,0:29:56.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, the good news -- alright.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:57.52,0:29:59.85,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.35,0:30:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,The good news is that the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:01.29,0:30:02.52,Default,,0,0,0,,session is not in fact going
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.52,0:30:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,three hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.77,0:30:07.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I just did that because if I set
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.15,0:30:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,the actual end time, the current
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.54,0:30:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,time would be too close to the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:10.57,0:30:12.64,Default,,0,0,0,,end time and they would -- the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:12.64,0:30:13.61,Default,,0,0,0,,event time would be hidden
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.61,0:30:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,because they'd be overlapping
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.76,0:30:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,otherwise.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.19,0:30:17.64,Default,,0,0,0,,But, here's another look at that
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.64,0:30:17.85,Default,,0,0,0,,code.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:17.85,0:30:19.26,Default,,0,0,0,,People viewing this at home
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.26,0:30:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,later are going to be very
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.06,0:30:21.23,Default,,0,0,0,,confused that you just dropped
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.23,0:30:22.92,Default,,0,0,0,,in right now, because the audio
Dialogue: 0,0:30:22.92,0:30:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,track seems a little bit off.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.18,0:30:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, and that's our demo.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.24,0:30:31.24,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:30:31.46,0:30:36.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Back to the slides.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:36.90,0:30:37.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so that's -- we've
Dialogue: 0,0:30:37.70,0:30:38.59,Default,,0,0,0,,talked about several new
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.59,0:30:39.94,Default,,0,0,0,,features in AVKit, and there are
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.94,0:30:40.82,Default,,0,0,0,,a couple more that I haven't
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.82,0:30:43.43,Default,,0,0,0,,talked about, but these are the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:43.43,0:30:44.40,Default,,0,0,0,,most important ones.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.19,0:30:47.24,Default,,0,0,0,,For more information about using
Dialogue: 0,0:30:47.24,0:30:49.55,Default,,0,0,0,,AVKit on tvOS, see last year's
Dialogue: 0,0:30:49.55,0:30:50.06,Default,,0,0,0,,session.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:50.73,0:30:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,And you can also join us in the
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.54,0:30:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,AVKit lab, shortly after this
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.44,0:30:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,session at 11, until 1, in Tech
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.21,0:30:57.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Lab F.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:58.58,0:30:59.73,Default,,0,0,0,,And bring us your questions.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.59,0:31:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, I'd like to introduce
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.05,0:31:03.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Marshall to the stage to talk
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.60,0:31:04.34,Default,,0,0,0,,about View Controller
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.34,0:31:04.95,Default,,0,0,0,,enhancements.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.52,0:31:10.13,Default,,0,0,0,,[ Applause ]
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.63,0:31:12.74,Default,,0,0,0,,>> Thank you, Dan.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.17,0:31:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,My name is Marshall, and today
Dialogue: 0,0:31:14.55,0:31:15.83,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm going to talk about View
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.83,0:31:17.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller Enhancements in tvOS
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.26,0:31:17.57,Default,,0,0,0,,11.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.57,0:31:18.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's dive right in.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.62,0:31:20.70,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we're going to take a
Dialogue: 0,0:31:20.70,0:31:22.18,Default,,0,0,0,,look at mobile presentations.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.41,0:31:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've ever used the UI Alert
Dialogue: 0,0:31:24.21,0:31:25.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller or put your Apple TV
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.70,0:31:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,to sleep, you might recognize
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.57,0:31:28.78,Default,,0,0,0,,this transition where we
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.78,0:31:30.25,Default,,0,0,0,,progressively blur the content
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.60,0:31:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and animate in the View
Dialogue: 0,0:31:31.53,0:31:32.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.45,0:31:35.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, starting in tvOS 11, you
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.03,0:31:36.06,Default,,0,0,0,,can now do that in your own
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.06,0:31:37.82,Default,,0,0,0,,applications, using the new UI
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.82,0:31:39.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Multi-Presentation Style called,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.35,0:31:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,.blurOverFullScreen.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.09,0:31:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This will progressively blur the
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.36,0:31:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,content of the presenting view
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.63,0:31:46.80,Default,,0,0,0,,controller, and it uses the same
Dialogue: 0,0:31:46.80,0:31:48.19,Default,,0,0,0,,timings in the animations that
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.19,0:31:49.50,Default,,0,0,0,,UI Alert Controller does.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.70,0:31:51.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Implementing this is easy.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.70,0:31:54.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You set the mobile presentation
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.10,0:31:55.83,Default,,0,0,0,,style to blur over full screen,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:55.83,0:31:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,and present your view
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.55,0:31:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,controller, like you normally
Dialogue: 0,0:31:57.74,0:31:57.97,Default,,0,0,0,,would.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:58.55,0:32:02.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Next, we're going to talk about
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.49,0:32:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,some enhancements, the UI Split
Dialogue: 0,0:32:03.99,0:32:04.64,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.15,0:32:06.64,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've used a split view
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.64,0:32:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,controller in your application
Dialogue: 0,0:32:08.08,0:32:11.71,Default,,0,0,0,,before, then you know that the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:11.71,0:32:12.99,Default,,0,0,0,,master view controller's on the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.99,0:32:13.96,Default,,0,0,0,,left, and the detailed view
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.96,0:32:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,controller's on the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.70,0:32:17.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, starting in tvOS 11, we
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.18,0:32:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,now have a new property that
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.26,0:32:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,will allow you to swap the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.13,0:32:19.55,Default,,0,0,0,,layout.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.89,0:32:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to support this, we
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.81,0:32:24.67,Default,,0,0,0,,have a new enum called UI Split
Dialogue: 0,0:32:24.67,0:32:26.08,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller Primary Edge
Dialogue: 0,0:32:26.08,0:32:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,with two values, leading and
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.89,0:32:28.40,Default,,0,0,0,,trailing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.22,0:32:30.86,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, a property that you
Dialogue: 0,0:32:30.86,0:32:32.19,Default,,0,0,0,,can set the primary edge.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.96,0:32:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, these names are important
Dialogue: 0,0:32:34.18,0:32:35.52,Default,,0,0,0,,because as we heard, tvOS now
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.52,0:32:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,supports RTL languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.83,0:32:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in this case, if you have a
Dialogue: 0,0:32:38.97,0:32:40.34,Default,,0,0,0,,left to right language and use
Dialogue: 0,0:32:40.34,0:32:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,leading, the master view
Dialogue: 0,0:32:41.15,0:32:42.34,Default,,0,0,0,,controller will be on the left,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.61,0:32:44.11,Default,,0,0,0,,and trailing the master view
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.11,0:32:44.93,Default,,0,0,0,,controller, would on the right.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:45.69,0:32:47.71,Default,,0,0,0,,But in RTL languages, those will
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.71,0:32:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,be mirrored, so the master would
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.00,0:32:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,be on the right, and for
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.91,0:32:57.58,Default,,0,0,0,,trailing, it will be on the
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.72,0:32:57.84,Default,,0,0,0,,left.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:57.84,0:32:59.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Last year, we announced a new
Dialogue: 0,0:32:59.33,0:33:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,use facing feature where users
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.74,0:33:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,can change their system
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.68,0:33:03.62,Default,,0,0,0,,appearance to dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:03.76,0:33:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,And this allows a great
Dialogue: 0,0:33:05.68,0:33:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,experience when their Apple TV's
Dialogue: 0,0:33:07.53,0:33:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,in a movie room or perhaps for
Dialogue: 0,0:33:09.19,0:33:09.79,Default,,0,0,0,,use at night.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.34,0:33:11.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, starting this year, we
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.52,0:33:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,have another mode which we call
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.44,0:33:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,automatic.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.21,0:33:15.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And what this will do, is it
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.87,0:33:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,will automatically change the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.35,0:33:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,user's system appearance to dark
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.36,0:33:22.02,Default,,0,0,0,,at night, and light during the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.02,0:33:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,day, based on their current
Dialogue: 0,0:33:23.37,0:33:23.91,Default,,0,0,0,,location.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.75,0:33:25.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, it's more important than
Dialogue: 0,0:33:25.78,0:33:27.23,Default,,0,0,0,,ever to make sure apps adopt the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.23,0:33:28.18,Default,,0,0,0,,light and dark appearance to
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.18,0:33:29.69,Default,,0,0,0,,offer the best user experience.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:30.52,0:33:31.55,Default,,0,0,0,,In order to support this, we've
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.55,0:33:32.75,Default,,0,0,0,,added some new APIs.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.17,0:33:34.30,Default,,0,0,0,,First, let's take a look at Top
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.30,0:33:34.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Shelf.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:36.84,0:33:38.85,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've provided a Top Shelf
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.85,0:33:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,extension, you know you can
Dialogue: 0,0:33:39.80,0:33:42.04,Default,,0,0,0,,provide an image URL to provide
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.23,0:33:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,images up in the Top Shelf.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.67,0:33:46.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, we are allowing a new API
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.66,0:33:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to provide a dark image asset as
Dialogue: 0,0:33:48.44,0:33:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,well, and the system will
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.44,0:33:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,automatically choose the correct
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.72,0:33:51.70,Default,,0,0,0,,asset to show, based on the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.70,0:33:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,system appearance.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.82,0:33:55.12,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you've looked into this
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.12,0:33:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,before, you have then a TV
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.51,0:33:58.32,Default,,0,0,0,,content item and then set the
Dialogue: 0,0:33:58.32,0:33:59.02,Default,,0,0,0,,image URL.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.77,0:34:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting in tvOS 11, you can now
Dialogue: 0,0:34:02.36,0:34:05.06,Default,,0,0,0,,call Set Image URL for traits
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.06,0:34:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and provide a light and dark
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.44,0:34:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,trait to provide those image
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.54,0:34:08.06,Default,,0,0,0,,assets.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:08.62,0:34:09.75,Default,,0,0,0,,If you'd like to still use the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.75,0:34:11.54,Default,,0,0,0,,same image, then you can just
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.54,0:34:12.83,Default,,0,0,0,,provide the same image URL to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:12.83,0:34:13.93,Default,,0,0,0,,both these method calls.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.52,0:34:17.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Finally, today, we're going to
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.75,0:34:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,talk about how you can adapt
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.99,0:34:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,your app's appearance to your
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.10,0:34:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,content.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.44,0:34:22.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We do this in our apps, such as
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.87,0:34:25.24,Default,,0,0,0,,our movies where if a movie has
Dialogue: 0,0:34:25.24,0:34:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,artwork that's light, we'll show
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.96,0:34:28.72,Default,,0,0,0,,appropriate controls, and if
Dialogue: 0,0:34:28.72,0:34:30.13,Default,,0,0,0,,it's dark, we'll also show
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.13,0:34:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,controls that look best on that.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:32.71,0:34:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, in order to make this
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.48,0:34:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,easier for developers, we have a
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.24,0:34:36.90,Default,,0,0,0,,new property on UI View
Dialogue: 0,0:34:36.90,0:34:38.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller, called Preferred
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.06,0:34:38.96,Default,,0,0,0,,User Interface Style.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.36,0:34:40.54,Default,,0,0,0,,If you've ever used preferred
Dialogue: 0,0:34:40.54,0:34:42.18,Default,,0,0,0,,status bar style, then this
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.18,0:34:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,might look familiar to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.10,0:34:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What it lets you do is specify a
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.80,0:34:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,specific UI User Interface
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.17,0:34:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Style, on your view controller,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:49.08,0:34:50.15,Default,,0,0,0,,which will customize the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.15,0:34:51.69,Default,,0,0,0,,appearance by updating the trait
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.69,0:34:53.47,Default,,0,0,0,,collection, and update the
Dialogue: 0,0:34:53.47,0:34:54.35,Default,,0,0,0,,system wallpaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:55.00,0:34:56.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a look at what this
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.20,0:34:56.62,Default,,0,0,0,,looks like.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.28,0:34:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, I've got a Tab-R
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.11,0:35:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,controller, where the first view
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.27,0:35:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,controller specifies a preferred
Dialogue: 0,0:35:01.93,0:35:03.41,Default,,0,0,0,,style of light, and the second
Dialogue: 0,0:35:03.56,0:35:05.27,Default,,0,0,0,,view controller specifies a
Dialogue: 0,0:35:05.27,0:35:06.22,Default,,0,0,0,,preferred style dark.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.59,0:35:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,When we switch tabs, we see that
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.00,0:35:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,the application's trait
Dialogue: 0,0:35:08.88,0:35:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,collection automatically get
Dialogue: 0,0:35:09.91,0:35:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,updated, as does the system
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.64,0:35:12.17,Default,,0,0,0,,wallpaper.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.08,0:35:15.66,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we've added three new API
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.66,0:35:16.84,Default,,0,0,0,,method for you to implement this
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.84,0:35:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in your own apps.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.95,0:35:19.74,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we have a read only
Dialogue: 0,0:35:19.74,0:35:21.45,Default,,0,0,0,,property, called Preferred User
Dialogue: 0,0:35:21.45,0:35:22.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Interface Style that you
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.53,0:35:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,override in your View
Dialogue: 0,0:35:23.44,0:35:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:24.22,0:35:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you can provide UI User
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.75,0:35:28.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Interfaced Style, light, dark,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.21,0:35:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,or unspecified, which means
Dialogue: 0,0:35:29.59,0:35:30.77,Default,,0,0,0,,follow the system style.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.57,0:35:33.06,Default,,0,0,0,,For most people, this is
Dialogue: 0,0:35:33.06,0:35:34.74,Default,,0,0,0,,probably enough to handle what
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.74,0:35:35.07,Default,,0,0,0,,you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.53,0:35:36.97,Default,,0,0,0,,But if you're using custom view
Dialogue: 0,0:35:36.97,0:35:38.32,Default,,0,0,0,,controllers, and using Child
Dialogue: 0,0:35:38.32,0:35:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,View Controller Containment,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:39.59,0:35:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,there's two more methods that
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.61,0:35:41.56,Default,,0,0,0,,you're going to want to use.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.62,0:35:43.41,Default,,0,0,0,,First, the Child View Controller
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.41,0:35:44.55,Default,,0,0,0,,For User Interface Style, let's
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.55,0:35:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,you delegate that decision to
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.90,0:35:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,review controller.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.01,0:35:48.52,Default,,0,0,0,,In the case of tab bar
Dialogue: 0,0:35:48.52,0:35:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,controller, the current selected
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.46,0:35:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,tab bar view controller -- or
Dialogue: 0,0:35:51.81,0:35:52.57,Default,,0,0,0,,the current selected View
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.57,0:35:54.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller, gets returned here.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.16,0:35:56.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, when that change
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.48,0:35:58.13,Default,,0,0,0,,occurs, you need to call Set
Dialogue: 0,0:35:58.13,0:35:59.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Needs User Interface Appearance
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.77,0:36:00.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Update.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.53,0:36:01.74,Default,,0,0,0,,This lets the system know that a
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.74,0:36:03.03,Default,,0,0,0,,change occurred and we can
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.03,0:36:04.33,Default,,0,0,0,,refigure out what the preferred
Dialogue: 0,0:36:04.33,0:36:05.38,Default,,0,0,0,,style's going to be for your
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.38,0:36:05.98,Default,,0,0,0,,application.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:09.30,0:36:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, those are our View
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.09,0:36:12.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Controller Enhancements today.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.91,0:36:14.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's take a look and see what
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.46,0:36:14.88,Default,,0,0,0,,we covered.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.42,0:36:17.11,Default,,0,0,0,,First, we learned that on-demand
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.11,0:36:18.49,Default,,0,0,0,,resources bundle size have been
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.49,0:36:19.90,Default,,0,0,0,,increased from 200 megabytes to
Dialogue: 0,0:36:19.90,0:36:21.27,Default,,0,0,0,,4 gigabytes that allow you to
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.27,0:36:22.53,Default,,0,0,0,,package more content on the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.53,0:36:23.87,Default,,0,0,0,,application install.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.82,0:36:26.70,Default,,0,0,0,,We learned that tvOS now
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.70,0:36:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,supports RTL languages, so make
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.35,0:36:29.59,Default,,0,0,0,,sure to use the tools we provide
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.59,0:36:31.90,Default,,0,0,0,,to test your layouts for those
Dialogue: 0,0:36:31.90,0:36:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,languages.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.97,0:36:35.41,Default,,0,0,0,,We learned about new ways to do
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.41,0:36:36.54,Default,,0,0,0,,work in the background to make
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.54,0:36:37.87,Default,,0,0,0,,sure that your content's always
Dialogue: 0,0:36:37.87,0:36:39.23,Default,,0,0,0,,updated and ready for the user
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.23,0:36:39.77,Default,,0,0,0,,when they launch your
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.77,0:36:40.39,Default,,0,0,0,,application.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.92,0:36:43.49,Default,,0,0,0,,We talked about new AVKit
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.49,0:36:44.58,Default,,0,0,0,,enhancements including, the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.58,0:36:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,custom info views.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.34,0:36:49.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We also saw a new API on Image
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.05,0:36:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Views, so you can make your
Dialogue: 0,0:36:50.57,0:36:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,content more interactive for the
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.69,0:36:53.02,Default,,0,0,0,,user.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.90,0:36:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,And finally, we talked about how
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.45,0:36:58.29,Default,,0,0,0,,to adapt your content, your
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.29,0:36:59.51,Default,,0,0,0,,application's appearance to your
Dialogue: 0,0:36:59.51,0:37:00.99,Default,,0,0,0,,content, using preferred user
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.99,0:37:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,interface style.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.24,0:37:04.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If you'd like any more
Dialogue: 0,0:37:04.19,0:37:05.85,Default,,0,0,0,,information, please develop --
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.85,0:37:06.55,Default,,0,0,0,,please visit
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.55,0:37:08.04,Default,,0,0,0,,developer.apple.com.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.00,0:37:10.28,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to expand on any of
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.28,0:37:11.25,Default,,0,0,0,,the topics we have, we have a
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.25,0:37:12.43,Default,,0,0,0,,lot of related sessions,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:12.43,0:37:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,including a few videos this
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.80,0:37:13.99,Default,,0,0,0,,year.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:14.94,0:37:16.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you for coming and I hope
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.07,0:37:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,you enjoy the rest of the
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.72,0:37:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,conference.
